 962          Computing the checksum is costly, that's why we rely on mtime comparisons. 
 963          Returns errcode: 
 964              0   - file is ok, it has either the specified mtime and size 
 965                            or checksum matches (then function sets mtime) 
 966              1   - file does not exist at all

 969          if not path: 
 970              return 1 
 971          abs_path = os.path.join(CFG.MOUNT_POINT, path) 
 972          try: 
 973              stat_info = os.stat(abs_path) 
 974          except OSError: 
 975              # File is missing completely 
 976              return 1 
 977   
 978          l_mtime = stat_info[stat.ST_MTIME] 
 979          l_size = stat_info[stat.ST_SIZE] 
 980          if l_mtime == mtime and l_size == size: 
 981              # Same mtime, and size, assume identity 
 982              return 0 
 983   
 984          # Have to check checksum 
 985          l_checksum = getFileChecksum(checksum_type, filename=abs_path) 
 986          if l_checksum != checksum: 
 987              return 2 
 988   
 989          # Set the mtime 
 990          os.utime(abs_path, (mtime, mtime)) 
 991          return 0
